{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.16",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 16 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:1",
      "text": "It is the part of man to prepare the soul: and of the Lord to govern the tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:2",
      "text": "All the ways of a man are open to his eyes: the Lord is the weigher of spirits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:3",
      "text": "Lay open thy works to the Lord: and thy thoughts shall be directed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:4",
      "text": "The Lord hath made all things for himself: the wicked also for the evil day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:5",
      "text": "Every proud man is an abomination to the Lord: though hand should be joined to hand, he is not innocent. The beginning of a good way is to do justice: and this is more acceptable with God, than to offer sacrifices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:6",
      "text": "By mercy and truth iniquity is redeemed; and by the fear of the Lord men depart from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:7",
      "text": "When the ways of man shall please the Lord, he will convert even his enemies to peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:8",
      "text": "Better is a little with justice, than great revenues with iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:9",
      "text": "The heart of man disposeth his way: but the Lord must direct his steps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:10",
      "text": "Divination is in the lips of the king, his mouth shall not err in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:11",
      "text": "Weight and balance are judgments of the Lord: and his work all the weights of the bag.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:12",
      "text": "They that act wickedly are abominable to the king: for the throne is established by justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:13",
      "text": "Just lips are the delight of kings: he that speaketh right things shall be loved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:14",
      "text": "The wrath of a king is as messengers of death: and the wise man will pacify it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:15",
      "text": "In the cheerfulness of the king's countenance is life: and his clemency is like the latter rain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:16",
      "text": "Get wisdom, because it is better than gold: and purchase prudence, for it is more precious than silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:17",
      "text": "The path of the just departeth from evils: he that keepeth his soul keepeth his way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:18",
      "text": "Pride goeth before destruction: and the spirit is lifted up before a fall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:19",
      "text": "It is better to be humbled with the meek, than to divide spoils with the proud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:20",
      "text": "The learned in word shall find good things: and he that trusteth in the Lord is blessed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:21",
      "text": "The wise in heart shall be called prudent: and he that is sweet in words, shall attain to greater things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:22",
      "text": "Knowledge is a fountain of life to him that possesseth it: the instruction of fools is foolishness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:23",
      "text": "The heart of the wise shall instruct his mouth: and shall add grace to his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:24",
      "text": "Well ordered words are as a honeycomb: sweet to the soul, and health to the bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:25",
      "text": "There is a way that seemeth to a man right: and the ends thereof lead to death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:26",
      "text": "The soul of him that laboureth, laboureth for himself, because his mouth hath obliged him to it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:27",
      "text": "The wicked man diggeth evil, and in his lips is a burning fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:28",
      "text": "A perverse man stirreth up quarrels: and one full of words separateth princes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:29",
      "text": "An unjust man allureth his friend: and leadeth him into a way that is not good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:30",
      "text": "He that with fixed eyes deviseth wicked things, biting his lips, bringeth evil to pass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:31",
      "text": "Old age is a crown of dignity, when it is found in the ways of justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:32",
      "text": "The patient man is better than the valiant: and he that ruleth his spirit, than he that taketh cities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.16.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 16:33",
      "text": "Lots are cast into the lap, but they are disposed of by the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
